             brought an Apron and a suit of Headclothes to him, but could not swear the Prisoner was the Person. The Prisoner deny'd the Fact, and said the Prosecutor had wrong'd her of 13 l. and call'd an Officer who deposed that he had arrested the Prosecutor in July last for 10 l. at the Prisoners Suit. Another deposed that he ask'd the Prosecutor why he did not serve the Warrant on her before, having taken it out 5 Months ago: to which the Prosecutor being call'd to answer reply'd, that he was inform'd by the Justice that he might do it when he pleased, and that he had not done it now but that he was inform'd that she was got into an ill Gang, some of which have been already Executed, and he was afraid of having his House broke open by her and her Accomplices. The Jury considering the whole matter found her <rs id="t17200907-6-verdict30" type="verdictDescription">
